article.description: — George Tinsley recorded 16 points as Binghamton beat New Hampshire 65-44 on Saturday.
article.headline: Defense shines as Binghamton routs New Hampshire 65-44
article.linkText: Defense shines as Binghamton routs New Hampshire 65-44
article.story: VESTAL, N.Y. -- — George Tinsley recorded 16 points as Binghamton beat New Hampshire 65-44 on Saturday. Brenton Mills added 10 points for the Bearcats, who held the Wildcats to 25.9% shooting, the lowest mark of the season for a Binghamton opponent. Thomas Bruce had four blocks for Binghamton (2-12, 2-9 America East Conference), which snapped its six-game losing streak. Tyler Bertram added six assists. New Hampshire scored 15 second-half points, a season low for the team. Blondeau Tchoukuiengo had 10 points for the Wildcats (7-7, 6-5). Nick Guadarrama added seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
